(285, 150, 'Family Packages', 'vn', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-size:48px\">Indochina within your reach</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Pull yourself away from the bustling daily life to seek for self-relaxation and let your mind wander with the clouds, to think less and feel more. Admire the beautiful scenery, the green primeval forests and go on an exciting adventure of your own. Participate in kayaking, cycling, hiking or interacting with the indigenous people. The simplicity, friendliness and hospitality that can be found anywhere in Indochina will make you eager to return for more.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>1. Visa and passport: </strong> Remember to check&nbsp;passport, visa and other documents to make sure they are good for travelling and keep soft copies of them in case they are lost, you can show the copies to the Embassy as proofs.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>2. Things to pack</strong>: The region&#39;s weather is relatively hot, so wear sunscreen, hat, swimsuit for swimming, comfortable shoes for walking and trekking, bring lightweight quick-dry clothing in hot season and some warm clothing&nbsp;in winter.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>3. Respect culture</strong>: Keep in mind to dress modestly and appropriately and take your footwear off when visiting local religious sites or temples.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>4. Watch belongings</strong>: In general, Indochina is a safe place for travelling, but you should keep an eye on your valuables in crowded places to avoid petty theft.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>5. Shop</strong>: Don&#39;t mind negotiating the price before buying things except at fixed price stores.</span></p>\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 'family-packages', 'Vietnam tour, Laos tour, Cambodia tour, Indochina tour, Greentours, Family Packages', 'Family Packages', 'Admire the beautiful scenery, the green primeval forests and go on an exciting adventure of your own. Participate in kayaking, cycling, hiking or interacting with the indigenous people. The simplicity and hospitality that can be found anywhere in Indochina will make you eager to return for more. '),
